The paper proposes a deep learning framework for estimating crowd density from static images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep and shallow, fully convolutional networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The testing on the UCF_CC_50 dataset indicates a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of multi-scale data augmentation suggests a potential focus on neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
